"Samie G., Bernier J., Rocher V., Lessard P.","Modeling nitrogen removal for a denitrification biofilter",2011,"Bioprocess and Biosystems Engineering","34","6",,"747","755",,,10.1007/s00449-011-0524-0,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79960459377&partnerID=40&md5=1cd5d039bf5f0c9a1bfd524bcc7e2484","Département de Génie Civil et Génie des Eaux, Université Laval, 1065 avenue de la Médecine, QC G1V 0A6, Canada; Syndicat Interdépartemental Pour l'Assainissement de l'Agglomération Parisienne, 2 rue Jules César, Paris CEDEX 75589 12, France","Samie, G., Département de Génie Civil et Génie des Eaux, Université Laval, 1065 avenue de la Médecine, QC G1V 0A6, Canada; Bernier, J., Département de Génie Civil et Génie des Eaux, Université Laval, 1065 avenue de la Médecine, QC G1V 0A6, Canada; Rocher, V., Syndicat Interdépartemental Pour l'Assainissement de l'Agglomération Parisienne, 2 rue Jules César, Paris CEDEX 75589 12, France; Lessard, P., Département de Génie Civil et Génie des Eaux, Université Laval, 1065 avenue de la Médecine, QC G1V 0A6, Canada","Nitrous oxide (N2O) is a major greenhouse gas, heavily contributing to global warming. N2O is emitted from various sources such as wastewater treatment plants, during the nitrification and denitrification steps. ASM models, which are commonly used in wastewater treatment, usually consider denitrification as a one-step process (NO 3 - directly reduced to N2) and are as such unable to provide values for intermediate products of the reaction like N 2O. In this study, a slightly modified ASM1 model was implemented in the GPS-X™ software to simulate the concentration of such intermediate products (NO2 -, NO and N2O) and to estimate the amounts of gaseous N2O emitted by the denitrification stage (12 biofilters) of the Seine-Centre WWTP (SIAAP, Paris). Simulations running on a 1-year period have shown good agreements with measured effluent data for nitrate and nitrite. The calculated mean value for emitted N2O is 4.95 kgN-N2O/day, which stands in the typical range of estimated experimental values of 4-31 kgN-N2O/day. Nitrous oxide emissions are usually not measured on WWTPs and so, as obtained results show, there is a certain potential for using models that quantify those emissions using traditionally measured influent data. © 2011 Springer-Verlag.","Biofilter; Denitrification; Modeling; Nitrous oxide; Wastewater treatment","Experimental values; Intermediate product; Mean values; Nitrification and denitrification; Nitrous oxide; Nitrous oxide emissions; One-step process; Wastewater treatment plants; Anesthetics; Biofilters; Biofiltration; Denitrification; Effluent treatment; Effluents; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Nitrogen; Nitrogen oxides; Reaction intermediates; Reclamation; Wastewater; Wastewater treatment; Water treatment plants; Nitrogen removal; nitrogen; alkalinity; article; biofilter; denitrification; greenhouse effect; mathematical analysis; mathematical model; methodology; nitrification; priority journal; simulation; waste water treatment plant; Computer Simulation; Denitrification; Models, Chemical; Nitrates; Nitrites; Nitrogen; Nitrogen Oxides; Paris; Software; Waste Disposal, Fluid; Water Purification",,"nitrogen, 7727-37-9; Nitrates; Nitrites; Nitrogen, 7727-37-9; Nitrogen Oxides",,,,"(2007) Climate Change 2007: The Physical Science Basis, , IPCC Contribution of Working Group I to the fourth assessment report of the intergovernmental panel on climate change. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York; (2007) Climate Change 2007: Mitigation, , IPCC Contribution of working group III to the fourth assessment report of the intergovernmental panel on climate change. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, , IPCC Contribution of working group I to the third assessment report of the intergovernmental panel on climate change. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, New York; Foley, J., De Haas, D., Yuan, Z